Where are you going to work as a Java developer?

Do you want to work on social software? Do you like a dynamic and fast growing organization? And would you like to work for a market leader in their field? Then I am looking for you!

Because of the large growth and strategy, I am looking for a Java developer. Since 2020, several suppliers within this industry have merged. All with one goal: a total software solution that serves parents and young children. The organisation is very informal and there are very short lines of communication. Work is based on Scrum Agile and there are 5 multidisciplinary development teams. They are currently about 110 people and the ambition is to grow to 125 employees. The organisation strives to work together as a team to achieve a good end result. The vision is clear, to further develop the product and continue to be the market leader in the coming years. The organisation is very informal and is basically a home-working organisation. Furthermore, there is plenty of parking space and fun outings are organised three times a year for both partner and child.

Functie

What will you be doing as a Java developer?

As a Java developer you will be working in 1 of our SCRUM teams. Currently there are about 30 developers working within our organisation and you will be building the bridge between different functionalities within our applications and integrating them into our central hub. You start your day at 9 am with a stand-up and then pick up your tasks for the day. Below are a number of tasks that you will be performing:

– Creating and developing features within the various applications

– Maintaining CI/CD pipelines

– Keeping busy with Security & Privacy

We work mainly from home and after Corona we intend to continue to do so as much as possible. We communicate via Trello and Slack and after corona we meet at the office one day a week.

